NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_IN_ALARM_T: An alarm will be issued to warn the operator about the issue if the signal power input from the RAN is too low or too high. Thus, immediate actions can be taken by the opreator.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_IN_ALC_TOO: ALC stands for Auto Level Control. ALC controls signal power for system protection when signal power input received from the RAN exceeds system tolerance.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_IN_ATT_TOO: Attenuator is used to manually control the signal power input from the RAN.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_UPLINK_OUT_ALARM_TH: An alarm will be issued to warn the operator about the issue if the signal power output to the RAN is too high. Thus, immediate actions can be taken by the opreator.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_UPLINK_OUT_ALC_TOOL: ALC stands for Auto Level Control. ALC controls signal power for system protection when signal power output to RAN exceeds the RAN tolerance.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_UPLINK_OUT_ATT_TOOL: Attenuator is used to manually control the signal power output to the RAN.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_OUT_ALARM_: If the signal power output is too low or too high, the alarm is generated so that the operator can detect the problem immediately. It is necessary to set the signal input lower limit value and input upper limit value.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_OUT_SHUTDO: If the signal power output continuously exceeds the permitted range of the system, system stop the output for a certain period of time to protect the system, especially the power amplifier.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_OUT_ALC_TO: ALC stands for Auto Level Control. ALC controls signal power for system protection when signal power output exceeds system tolerance.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_DOWNLINK_OUT_ATT_TO: Attenuator is used to manually control the signal power output.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_UPLINK_IN_SHUTDOWN_: If the signal power input continuously exceeds the permitted range of the system, system stop the input for a certain period of time to protect the system, especially the low noise amplifier.
NODE.UPDATE_RF_PORT_MODAL_UPLINK_IN_ALC_TOOLT: ALC stands for Auto Level Control. ALC controls signal power for system protection when signal power input exceeds system tolerance.
